{{Infobox language |name=Ikobi |nativename=Mena |region=[[Papua New Guinea]] |speakers={{sigfig|1570|2}} |date=2009 |ref=e18 |familycolor=Papuan |fam1=[[Papuan Gulf languages|Papuan Gulf]] ? |fam2=Kikorian |fam3=[[Turama–Kikorian languages|Turama–Kikorian]] |fam4=Turama |iso3=meb |glotto=ikob1240 |glottorefname=Ikobi-Mena }} '''Ikobi''', or '''Ikobi-Mena''' after its two varieties, is a [[Papuan language]], or pair of languages, of [[Papua New Guinea]]. Wurm and Hattori (1981) treat the two varieties, Ikobi and Mena, as distinct languages, but ''Ethnologue'' 16 judges them to be one.
