{{Infobox language |name=Kaba So |nativename=Kulfa |states=[[Chad]] |speakers={{sigfig|7130|2}} |date=1993 census |ref=e18 |speakers2=4,030 Koulfa, 2,200 Kurumi, 910 Bara (1993 census)<ref name=e18/> |familycolor=Nilo-Saharan |fam2=[[Central Sudanic]] |fam3=[[Bongo–Bagirmi languages|Bongo–Bagirmi]] |fam4=[[Kaba languages|Kaba]] |iso3=kxj |glotto=kulf1238 |glottorefname=Kulfa |dia1=Bara |dia2=Kulfa |dia3=Kurumi }}
'''Kaba So''', also known as '''Kulfa''' after its primary dialect, is a [[Bongo–Bagirmi language]] of [[Chad]]. It is nearly intelligible with [[Kaba Na language|Kaba Na]], which is used as a second language.
