{{Infobox language family |name=Koch |region=[[India]] |familycolor=Sino-Tibetan |fam2=[[Sal languages|Brahmaputran]] |fam3=[[Bodo–Garo languages|Bodo–Garo]] |glotto=koch1249 |glottorefname=Kochic }}
The '''Koch languages''' are a small group of [[Sino-Tibetan languages]] spoken in northeastern India. They are: *[[Atong language (Sino-Tibetan)|Atong]] *[[Koch language|Koch]] *[[Ruga language|Ruga]] *[[Rabha language|Rabha]]
The [[Rajbongshi people|Rajbongshi]], who currently speak an [[Indo-Aryan languages|Indo-Aryan language]], used to speak a Koch language.
